# Overview
This project is a backend REST API developed in Python using FastAPI.
It consumes data from the external API RandomUser and exposes a clean JSON endpoint returning a list of people.

The focus of this solution is backend development, following good practices such as:
async I/O
external API integration
error handling
API documentation

# Virtual Environment

Create virtual environment:
py -m venv .venv

Activate:
.\.venv\Scripts\activate

# Install Dependencies

Upgrade pip and install packages:
py -m pip install --upgrade pip
py -m pip install -r requirements.txt

# Start the FastAPI
py -m uvicorn src.app.main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8001 --reload

# API documentation (Swagger)
FastAPI automatically provides an interactive API documentation with Swagger.

Once the server is running, Swagger is available at the following link:
http://127.0.0.1:8001/docs

# Thunder Client (VS Code)

The API can also be tested using Thunder Client tool provided by VS Code.

Get people list:
http://127.0.0.1:8001/people
